reviews.text: For the “all you can eat dinner” you get what you pay for. At the start the stuff comes out really good but as you keep ordering the quality of the food really goes down. Some days it can be really consistent, while other nights it’s bad all around. Sometimes the waiters will forget to bring you the right amount of food you ordered. The tablet idea is a cool concept but feels like you don’t even have a waiter. But I can say the shrimp tempura is the best thing on the menu and is the one item that always comes out hot and fresh. The sushi is pretty standard.
Have been here for long. Food quality is good for the price. Sufficient side dishes for set

html_attributions: 貓仔減肥記の尋回鎖骨的日子Jackie Choi

reviews.text: I really do like it here. The staff are friendly and the food is really decent and reasonably priced unlike places like Central where it's all overpriced. I like how they let us choose our own sake glasses, (with a good variety for photo options!) and my tea cup was never empty. The green tea kept coming, almost a bit too much, but I love how attentive the staff are and how the manager was having sake shots with other customers. It all just seemed really nice and relaxed which is always nice to see, and always makes me appreciate Kennedy Town.
Sincere and geniune service, ambience atmosphere and outstanding food there.  Only one thing need to improve is....air con....  We were too hot when dining there.
Be here many times and never stopped to get good food except this time, I think there is a new manager and the service wasn't as good as before
Recommended Japanese restaurant in Kennedy Town. Good quality food at reasonable prices. Service is good.
Good food, good meeting place, reasonable price.
